WEBVTT

00:09.625 --> 00:12.583
The boat was full of weapons.
Rocket launchers, assault rifles.

00:12.667 --> 00:13.875
Military grade. European, I think.

00:13.958 --> 00:15.167
[Fisk] Who knew what was in that ship?

00:15.250 --> 00:17.208
[Buck] Only the Captain
and the First Mate.

00:17.292 --> 00:21.583
The people I work for are very grateful
for the use of your port.

00:21.667 --> 00:25.458
[Matt] If Fisk gets the guns off the boat
into Red Hook, they disappear.

00:25.542 --> 00:27.458
-You know what to do.
-[Karen gasps]

00:28.042 --> 00:29.125
[Daredevil] He killed them all.

00:29.208 --> 00:30.375
[woman on TV] Fisk is tough.

00:30.458 --> 00:32.500
He's getting in the ring this weekend,
isn't he?

00:34.083 --> 00:35.542
Daredevil got away.

00:37.125 --> 00:38.125
-Get in!
-[clamoring]

00:38.208 --> 00:39.833
[Buck] Apparently, someone is helping him.

00:39.917 --> 00:42.542
-[thuds]
-Someone with very good aim.

00:42.625 --> 00:45.833
Have you ever been in the same room
with Benjamin Poindexter?

00:46.458 --> 00:48.083
I have.

00:48.167 --> 00:49.792
[man] Can I help you?

00:49.875 --> 00:50.875
[Dex] Father, I--

00:50.958 --> 00:52.667
I need absolution.

00:52.750 --> 00:53.917
[♪ eerie music playing]

01:02.875 --> 01:05.000
[♪ "New York State of Mind"
by Billy Joel playing]

01:12.292 --> 01:13.375
[stove clicking]

01:25.458 --> 01:27.167
[pan sizzling]

01:47.417 --> 01:49.083
[bones cracking]

01:54.333 --> 01:55.750
[soft cracking]

01:59.625 --> 02:01.792
♪ Some folks like to get away ♪

02:01.875 --> 02:05.833
♪ Take a holiday from the neighborhood ♪

02:07.625 --> 02:12.167
♪ Hop a flight to Miami Beach
or to Hollywood ♪

02:14.375 --> 02:15.917
Ah, Tony.

02:16.000 --> 02:17.833
Good morning, Mrs. Smithers.

02:18.917 --> 02:21.292
-[Mrs. Smithers] Aw! [chuckles]
-[meows]

02:24.000 --> 02:27.542
♪ I'm in a New York state of mind ♪

02:28.917 --> 02:31.167
Such a nice boy.

02:31.250 --> 02:32.625
Have a nice day.

02:34.250 --> 02:36.042
[whistling "New York State of Mind"]

02:36.125 --> 02:38.458
♪ I've seen all the movie stars ♪

02:38.542 --> 02:42.208
♪ In their fancy cars
and their limousines ♪

02:42.292 --> 02:43.583
[continues whistling]

02:43.667 --> 02:46.167
-[coin clinks]
-[coins jingling]

02:46.250 --> 02:48.583
♪ Under the evergreens ♪

02:51.583 --> 02:53.750
♪ I know what I'm needing ♪

02:53.833 --> 02:55.500
[bell dinging]

02:59.750 --> 03:00.875
[soft chattering]

03:12.542 --> 03:13.833
[sighs]

03:27.833 --> 03:29.250
You ready?

03:30.250 --> 03:32.042
What are you famous for?

03:32.625 --> 03:36.792
[sighs] I mean, the milkshakes are good.

03:37.458 --> 03:38.708
-Excellent.
-[waitress] Mm-hmm.

03:38.792 --> 03:40.000
I'll have, uh...

03:41.417 --> 03:43.750
-one banana milkshake.
-[waitress scribbling]

03:43.833 --> 03:45.417
You want whip?

03:46.792 --> 03:48.375
Doesn't everybody?

03:49.750 --> 03:50.750
[sighs]

03:50.833 --> 03:52.750
[♪ soft jazz music playing over speaker]

04:12.708 --> 04:14.833
[machine whirs]

04:21.250 --> 04:23.083
[operator] Task Force hotline.
What's your emergency?

04:23.167 --> 04:25.750
I think I just saw Frank Castle

04:25.833 --> 04:29.125
enter Bel Aire Diner at 43rd and 10th.

04:29.208 --> 04:30.292
[operator] The Punisher?

04:30.375 --> 04:31.375
Are you sure?

04:31.458 --> 04:32.750
Oh, yeah.

04:33.250 --> 04:34.542
Yeah, it's him.

04:34.625 --> 04:35.875
[operator] Task force is en route.

04:35.958 --> 04:37.125
Shit.

04:37.208 --> 04:38.708
He has a gun.

04:39.458 --> 04:40.833
-Try to find a safe place--
-[phone beeps]

04:40.917 --> 04:42.417
[whirring]

04:52.833 --> 04:54.167
[hissing]

05:00.792 --> 05:02.042
[waitress] There you go.

05:02.125 --> 05:03.292
Thank you.

05:14.917 --> 05:16.167
[sucking]

05:22.667 --> 05:24.875
-[slurps]
-[sirens approaching]

05:34.792 --> 05:37.042
[sirens blaring]

05:38.833 --> 05:39.917
[officer] Entry team get prepped.

05:40.000 --> 05:41.083
Let's do it. Let's get...

05:41.167 --> 05:42.583
-On your six!
-[officer 2] On me, on me!

05:42.667 --> 05:44.250
[officers shouting indistinctly]

05:45.250 --> 05:46.458
[officer] Everybody, stay in your seats!

05:46.542 --> 05:47.875
-Keep your hands up!
-[officer 2] Hey! Hey!

05:47.958 --> 05:49.583
-[officer 3] Everyone, sit down!
-[officer 2] Don't move!

05:49.667 --> 05:51.917
-[officer 4] Nobody leaves! Nobody leaves!
-[officer 5] Throw 'em down!

05:52.000 --> 05:53.500
-Down!
-[clamoring]

05:53.583 --> 05:54.958
-[officer 4] Let's go!
-Stay down!

05:56.500 --> 05:58.125
-[officer 4] Nobody fucking move.
-[officer 3] You got eyes?

05:58.208 --> 05:59.833
-I got nothin'.
-[officer 4] What's in the back?

05:59.917 --> 06:01.167
-[officer 6] Clear!
-[officer 4] Max?

06:01.250 --> 06:02.250
[officer 7] Clear!

06:03.833 --> 06:05.250
[officer 4] Yo!

06:05.333 --> 06:06.333
Milkshake!

06:07.375 --> 06:08.833
Put your goddamn hands up.

06:08.917 --> 06:10.125
Turn around now.

06:10.625 --> 06:11.875
Let's go!

06:14.208 --> 06:16.000
[chair squeaks]

06:16.083 --> 06:17.083
[softly] What...

06:17.167 --> 06:18.542
-[blows]
-[grunts]

06:18.625 --> 06:20.542
[♪ "New York State of Mind"
by Billy Joel continues]

06:20.625 --> 06:23.250
[officers grunting]

06:23.333 --> 06:24.667
[Bullseye grunts]

06:25.458 --> 06:27.125
[both grunting]

06:27.208 --> 06:28.875
-[officer 8] Stop resisting!
-[officer 9] Now!

06:30.167 --> 06:31.792
[Bullseye grunts]

06:34.375 --> 06:36.833
♪ I don't have any reasons ♪

06:37.292 --> 06:38.708
[waitress groaning]

06:38.792 --> 06:40.208
♪ I left them all behind ♪

06:40.292 --> 06:42.500
-[Bullseye grunting]
-[utensil stabs]

06:44.042 --> 06:45.500
[Bullseye] That was a great milkshake.

06:47.042 --> 06:49.625
[gurgling, choking]

06:50.708 --> 06:51.875
[screams in pain]

06:53.208 --> 06:56.542
[Bullseye grunting]

06:58.875 --> 07:00.375
[gasps]

07:03.042 --> 07:05.708
[grunting]

07:07.625 --> 07:09.875
-[dog barking]
-[Bullseye] Huh?

07:09.958 --> 07:11.667
-[grunts]
-[dog barks]

07:11.750 --> 07:13.083
[whines]

07:23.000 --> 07:25.708
Dogs in restaurants are unsanitary.

07:27.292 --> 07:28.667
[voice shaking] Please don't...

07:28.750 --> 07:29.792
kill me.

07:32.917 --> 07:34.917
[breathing heavily, grunting]

07:35.542 --> 07:37.042
Oh, don't worry.

07:37.833 --> 07:40.500
[screams, groans]

07:41.833 --> 07:43.333
I'm one of the good guys.

07:43.417 --> 07:45.250
♪ I'm just taking a Greyhound ♪

07:45.333 --> 07:46.375
[whines]

07:46.458 --> 07:47.875
♪ On the Hudson River Line ♪

07:47.958 --> 07:49.458
[man over radio] Negative.
Can we know get an...

07:49.542 --> 07:50.792
It's fucking Bullseye!

07:51.708 --> 07:53.667
It's Bullseye! It's-- [grunts]

07:57.375 --> 07:58.375
[chuckles]

07:58.958 --> 07:59.958
[whines]

08:00.042 --> 08:01.833
♪ 'Cause I'm in ♪

08:06.875 --> 08:09.083
♪ I'm in a New York ♪

08:09.167 --> 08:11.583
[ketchup bottle squirts]

08:11.667 --> 08:17.500
♪ State of mind ♪

08:17.583 --> 08:18.917
[doorbell dinging]

08:19.542 --> 08:23.458
♪ Yeah, yeah ♪

08:36.333 --> 08:38.417
[♪ theme music playing]

10:17.375 --> 10:19.375
[City Without Fear voice] It's me again.

10:19.458 --> 10:21.292
A cringe explosion in the East River?

10:21.375 --> 10:22.833
Don't worry about it!

10:22.917 --> 10:24.083
Floating dead bodies?

10:24.167 --> 10:25.750
Don't worry about it.

10:25.833 --> 10:29.500
All smoke and mirrors,
distracting you from the main event!

10:29.583 --> 10:31.417
-My charity boxing match...
-[bell dings]

10:31.500 --> 10:35.250
...that's raising money for a New York
Born Again revitalization project,

10:35.333 --> 10:36.792
that is really a shell corporation
for money laundering

10:36.875 --> 10:38.958
to offshore accounts
that make my friends grotesquely rich.

10:39.042 --> 10:40.167
[breathing heavily]

10:40.250 --> 10:44.083
I've been training hard at the gym
for you, New York.

10:44.167 --> 10:45.708
The money we will raise will go to

10:45.792 --> 10:46.792
arresting you without due process,

10:46.875 --> 10:48.000
seizing your property
for my personal gain,

10:48.083 --> 10:50.083
locking up your loved ones,
and so much more.

10:50.167 --> 10:52.625
Back to the gym, I go, because

10:52.708 --> 10:55.208
I love you, New York!

10:55.750 --> 10:58.167
[horns blaring distantly]

10:58.250 --> 11:01.083
[officer] We're getting split
by coordinates. Nothing to report.

11:02.750 --> 11:05.208
[Soledad] My name is Soledad Ayala.

11:05.292 --> 11:07.958
I am a nurse from Washington Heights.

11:08.042 --> 11:10.500
I was arrested by the Task Force,

11:10.583 --> 11:13.333
the same people who killed my husband.

11:14.292 --> 11:15.292
I am the missing.

11:16.583 --> 11:17.833
But I will not back down.

11:18.917 --> 11:19.917
I will stay...

11:20.625 --> 11:21.667
and fight.

11:22.542 --> 11:25.042
-[device beeps]
-[Karen] It's okay. Thank you.

11:25.125 --> 11:26.583
[Jack] It's time for me to go.

11:26.667 --> 11:28.125
I wish you'd reconsider.

11:28.208 --> 11:31.750
[chuckles] I have been
in a cage for... [sighs]

11:31.833 --> 11:33.750
...six months.

11:33.833 --> 11:37.042
I need to shower.
I need to burn these clothes. [sighs]

11:37.125 --> 11:38.542
I'm too old for this shit.

11:38.625 --> 11:41.292
Ah, it's a shame 'cause we could use
more people like you.

11:42.458 --> 11:43.458
Like me?

11:45.333 --> 11:46.792
You don't realize it, do you?

11:47.958 --> 11:49.250
You're not a hero.

11:50.250 --> 11:51.833
You're a symbol now.

11:51.917 --> 11:53.750
Hope for an entire city.

11:55.667 --> 11:56.667
It's true.

11:57.542 --> 11:59.250
I gave Karen an account number.

11:59.333 --> 12:00.917
Use whatever you need,

12:01.000 --> 12:02.083
whenever you need it.

12:02.167 --> 12:03.292
Thank you.

12:03.375 --> 12:04.750
Good luck, my friend.

12:05.833 --> 12:07.542
-Destroy them both.
-[chuckles]

12:11.958 --> 12:13.625
-[Angela] Hey.
-Hey.

12:13.708 --> 12:14.875
What you got there?

12:14.958 --> 12:17.583
Uh, SD card.
I'm supposed to get it to my source,

12:17.667 --> 12:18.833
but with the Task Force everywhere,

12:18.917 --> 12:20.417
-I'm too exposed.
-It's okay.

12:21.250 --> 12:22.500
Let me do it.

12:22.583 --> 12:25.625
-[chuckles] Absolutely not.
-Oh, come on.

12:26.542 --> 12:29.542
[whispering] No, come on, I just need
to do this for my aunt, please.

12:31.167 --> 12:33.667
[sighs] No way. It's too dangerous.

12:34.625 --> 12:35.625
So what?

12:35.708 --> 12:37.042
I stole their truck.

12:37.125 --> 12:39.833
[whispering] They're probably already
looking for me. [chuckles softly]

12:39.917 --> 12:41.792
[♪ tense music playing]

12:45.083 --> 12:46.333
[Karen sighs]

12:50.667 --> 12:51.750
Thank you.

12:51.833 --> 12:52.958
Be careful.

13:02.417 --> 13:03.417
[inhales sharply]

13:05.875 --> 13:06.917
[sighs]

13:07.875 --> 13:09.333
[soft clinking]

13:12.583 --> 13:14.917
Do you understand the responsibility
that comes with this?

13:16.542 --> 13:17.583
Yeah,

13:17.667 --> 13:18.708
I do.

13:19.833 --> 13:20.958
Are you ready?

13:22.292 --> 13:23.292
[chuckles]

13:24.250 --> 13:25.250
Were you?

13:25.750 --> 13:27.458
[rumbling]

13:27.542 --> 13:29.500
-[heart thumping]
-[heavy breathing]

13:30.458 --> 13:31.875
[whispering] Everybody, stay still.

13:40.333 --> 13:42.708
-[thumping continues]
-[♪ tense music playing]

13:47.292 --> 13:48.417
[creaking]

13:49.875 --> 13:51.833
[man yells, grunts]

13:53.458 --> 13:55.917
[gasps] My name is Christofi Savva.

13:56.000 --> 13:57.458
I'm here to help. [gasps]

13:57.542 --> 13:59.958
I was the First Mate on the Northern Star.

14:01.042 --> 14:02.583
[breathes heavily]

14:10.250 --> 14:11.250
[kisses]

14:11.875 --> 14:14.083
That's one way to deal with the Governor.

14:15.958 --> 14:17.250
It's for the journey,

14:17.333 --> 14:18.333
not the meeting.

14:18.417 --> 14:20.542
Marge and I have a rapport.

14:23.417 --> 14:25.375
And I appreciate you talkin' to her.

14:27.125 --> 14:28.542
I know what you're doing.

14:29.833 --> 14:31.208
Arranging this

14:31.292 --> 14:33.583
trip to Albany just before the fight.

14:35.833 --> 14:37.125
I don't like it...

14:38.458 --> 14:40.708
when you send me away and shut me out.

14:42.625 --> 14:44.000
This is not that.

14:44.083 --> 14:45.667
It's a public place.

14:47.792 --> 14:49.917
Too much could go wrong.

14:52.458 --> 14:54.167
We're a matched set.

14:54.708 --> 14:56.292
I should be there tonight.

15:00.250 --> 15:01.875
I'll call you when it's over.

15:03.583 --> 15:05.250
[inhales deeply]

15:10.417 --> 15:13.208
[♪ eerie music playing]

15:31.500 --> 15:32.583
Good luck.

15:40.292 --> 15:43.458
[door opens, shuts]

15:44.333 --> 15:46.708
[Christofi] You were captured
only for helping me.

15:49.583 --> 15:51.625
I would like to return that kindness.

15:54.083 --> 15:56.500
What can you tell us
about the Northern Star?

15:58.000 --> 15:59.083
Everything.

16:00.042 --> 16:02.250
The illegal weapons, the fake documents...

16:05.958 --> 16:08.542
Can you connect any of it to Fisk?

16:12.083 --> 16:13.375
We were protected.

16:14.042 --> 16:16.875
All the paperwork was signed off by...

16:18.125 --> 16:19.667
Vasillias tou Enklimatos.

16:21.208 --> 16:22.625
The Kingpin.

16:29.375 --> 16:31.625
Well, we need an attorney
to take his statement.

16:33.542 --> 16:35.250
-[sighs] Kirsten...
-Yeah, yeah.

16:35.333 --> 16:36.667
Well, it's too dangerous
to bring Christofi to her,

16:36.750 --> 16:38.042
so she'll have to come to us.

16:38.125 --> 16:40.542
Won't be too hard. All the Task Force
will be at the fight tonight.

16:40.625 --> 16:41.875
Yeah, yeah.

16:41.958 --> 16:43.375
At Fogwell's.

16:46.542 --> 16:48.667
Some of the last memories
of my father are in that gym.

16:49.542 --> 16:51.667
[sighs] Now, it's crawling
with Task Force.

16:52.500 --> 16:53.833
Yeah, he wants me there.

16:54.333 --> 16:57.042
-[inhales deeply]
-Or...

16:57.917 --> 16:59.083
Not just me.

16:59.167 --> 17:00.208
The whole fight--

17:00.292 --> 17:01.542
He's setting a trap for Bullseye.

17:02.292 --> 17:03.542
[sighs] Oh, fuck.

17:05.333 --> 17:07.083
-[grunts] I'm gonna find Bullseye.
-Mm-hmm.

17:07.167 --> 17:09.042
-You just connect Kirsten and Christofi.
-Christofi.

17:09.125 --> 17:10.292
Yep. [sighs]

17:10.375 --> 17:12.167
-All right. Be careful.
-You, too.

17:15.125 --> 17:16.250
I love you.

17:19.167 --> 17:20.375
I love you, too.

17:24.458 --> 17:26.125
[reporter] I'm here outside Fogwell's Gym,

17:26.208 --> 17:30.542
a part of Mayor Fisk's Born Again
revitalization project,

17:30.625 --> 17:32.958
and host to tonight's benefit boxing match

17:33.042 --> 17:34.917
between the Mayor and heavyweight

17:35.000 --> 17:36.917
Mike "the Matterhorn" Melendez.

17:37.000 --> 17:39.292
Due to the recent spate
of vigilante violence,

17:39.375 --> 17:40.917
I'm told security will be tight,

17:41.000 --> 17:43.167
-with increased Task Force to--
-[shatters]

17:44.333 --> 17:45.625
[Kirsten] No, I don't understand.

17:45.708 --> 17:48.542
I was under the impression
that that account was paid in full.

17:49.708 --> 17:51.625
[shouting] Down on the fucking ground now!

17:51.708 --> 17:54.458
Down on the fucking ground!
Out of your fucking chairs! Down!

17:54.542 --> 17:56.250
-On the fucking ground! Down!
-[Kirsten] Hey! Hey!

17:56.333 --> 17:59.958
You assholes better have a warrant, or
I'm gonna bury you under so many lawsuits

18:00.042 --> 18:03.792
that your grandchildren's grandchildren
will still be paying your legal bills.

18:03.875 --> 18:05.042
-Safer Streets.
-[objects clattering]

18:05.125 --> 18:08.250
-I don't need a warrant or probable cause.
-We won't even need to knock.

18:09.000 --> 18:10.000
You again?

18:11.125 --> 18:12.750
-[Powell] Where's your client?
-[Kirsten] Which one?

18:12.833 --> 18:15.167
[Powell] Terrorist fugitive Jack Duquesne,
also known as Swordsman.

18:15.250 --> 18:18.042
-Allegedly.
-A court of law found him guilty.

18:18.667 --> 18:19.833
That was no court.

18:20.333 --> 18:22.167
Whatever.
I'm not gonna fucking ask you again.

18:22.250 --> 18:23.625
Do you see him here? Anywhere?

18:23.708 --> 18:27.167
Maybe he's hiding under a pile of files
or that wall made of glass.

18:27.250 --> 18:28.292
Nothing, sir.

18:29.750 --> 18:31.000
You hear from him, you turn him in.

18:31.083 --> 18:32.875
Attorney-client privilege still applies.

18:32.958 --> 18:35.667
I don't give a fuck about your
attorney-client whatever the fuck.

18:35.750 --> 18:37.750
He was part of a terrorist attack
that killed 25 men

18:37.833 --> 18:39.333
-on board that ship.
-Bullshit.

18:39.917 --> 18:41.125
Talk like that will get you hurt someday.

18:41.208 --> 18:43.167
Talk like that is how I do my fucking job.

18:45.875 --> 18:48.542
You tell Matt Murdock we said hello. Okay?

18:52.667 --> 18:53.750
See you around, Counselor!

18:55.250 --> 18:56.250
[clatters]

18:59.583 --> 19:01.625
[Fisk] First, Bullseye and now this.

19:01.708 --> 19:02.958
And how many escaped?

19:03.042 --> 19:04.417
Nineteen in total.

19:04.875 --> 19:06.750
[sighs] I've had enough!

19:07.750 --> 19:10.333
There's leaks in Red Hook,
leaks in City Hall!

19:10.417 --> 19:11.792
You need to find them, Buck!

19:11.875 --> 19:13.208
Plug them!

19:13.292 --> 19:14.375
Every one!

19:15.750 --> 19:17.500
-How much you wanna know?
-Enough to know what's--

19:17.583 --> 19:18.750
[Charles] You know what I wanna know?

19:19.375 --> 19:20.625
Why... [munching]

19:20.708 --> 19:22.708
...is wombat shit cube-shaped?

19:23.500 --> 19:25.167
I mean, it's the strangest thing
I've ever seen.

19:26.042 --> 19:28.500
Apparently, they like to
stack it into, like,

19:28.583 --> 19:32.458
little walls that mark
their territory. [laughs]

19:32.542 --> 19:33.625
Isn't that weird?

19:33.708 --> 19:36.875
Little Lego walls of wombat shit

19:36.958 --> 19:38.125
to get the bitches.

19:38.208 --> 19:39.458
They literally shit bricks.

19:40.917 --> 19:44.208
Charles, you are not on my agenda.

19:44.292 --> 19:47.250
I have another awesome
existential question.

19:48.125 --> 19:50.375
Why is my non-cube shitting ass

19:50.458 --> 19:52.708
sitting on a pile of HK 416s

19:52.792 --> 19:56.417
and rocket launchers,
and other assorted weapons, when this,

19:56.500 --> 19:59.583
all of this, is not supposed to be
in a warehouse in Brooklyn.

19:59.667 --> 20:03.292
It's supposed to be on its way to
Guinea-Bissau to win the hearts and minds.

20:03.375 --> 20:05.708
Because Daredevil knows it's in New York.

20:06.417 --> 20:07.542
[Charles] People need these arms.

20:08.083 --> 20:09.750
Shots must be fired.

20:10.667 --> 20:12.750
If you put these on another boat,

20:12.833 --> 20:15.750
we'll have the Northern Star
all over again, or worse.

20:15.833 --> 20:19.125
And I don't need my city
turning on me. Not now.

20:19.208 --> 20:21.375
Your city. [laughs]

20:21.458 --> 20:23.167
-That's rich.
-Do not mock me!

20:23.250 --> 20:25.667
It is a big world out there, sailor.

20:25.750 --> 20:30.500
With big wars and much, much bigger stakes
than one elected official.

20:30.583 --> 20:32.958
Official who gave you access
to an American free port.

20:33.042 --> 20:35.458
And on behalf of the agency,
we appreciate your service.

20:35.542 --> 20:38.833
A service, I might remind you,
which is yet to be rendered.

20:39.458 --> 20:41.542
I will honor our arrangement.

20:42.208 --> 20:43.333
Well, that's great.

20:43.417 --> 20:45.708
I mean, the question kind of becomes
"Can you?" Right?

20:45.792 --> 20:49.500
I mean, you've been rocking and rolling
with all your big cat friends.

20:49.583 --> 20:52.917
And then Uncle Sam shows up,
and your facility, the...

20:53.000 --> 20:57.167
the golden fucking goose is cooked
because this place is compromised.

20:57.250 --> 21:00.375
And your Governor is threatening
to revoke its charter.

21:00.458 --> 21:02.167
You are overreaching.

21:02.250 --> 21:03.792
[Charles] From where I'm sitting,

21:03.875 --> 21:05.583
it seems to me you're having a--

21:05.667 --> 21:09.375
[grunts] Just a very difficult time
controlling...

21:10.083 --> 21:13.083
your very, very small piece of the world.

21:13.167 --> 21:14.708
I am not your employee!

21:15.625 --> 21:17.000
[breathes deeply]

21:18.583 --> 21:19.667
I never said you were.

21:20.458 --> 21:23.792
Partners, Wilson--
Come on! We're partners.

21:23.875 --> 21:25.958
Hey, I don't respond well to threats.

21:26.042 --> 21:27.333
[chuckling] That's not a threat.

21:29.417 --> 21:31.042
Look, neither of us ever walk in anywhere

21:31.125 --> 21:33.458
without knowing how we're gonna get out.

21:33.542 --> 21:36.208
[chuckles] It's adorable,
but you can put your hands down.

21:37.208 --> 21:38.292
You're right.

21:38.917 --> 21:41.458
-[officers grunt]
-[bodies thudding]

21:43.375 --> 21:46.625
[Fisk] Your shipment will be delivered
when the time is right.

21:47.167 --> 21:49.667
I would ask that you practice patience!

21:53.708 --> 21:55.583
Next time you wanna see me, call.

21:57.292 --> 21:58.292
It's courteous.

22:05.458 --> 22:08.083
-[door shuts]
-Shit.

22:09.167 --> 22:10.708
This was retaliation,

22:10.792 --> 22:13.042
and then our accounts
are mysteriously frozen.

22:13.125 --> 22:14.417
It's not a coincidence.

22:14.500 --> 22:15.917
I wouldn't be here if it wasn't important.

22:16.000 --> 22:17.125
Yeah. Well, the last time I helped you,

22:17.208 --> 22:19.333
I ended up as an accessory
to a terrorist attack.

22:19.417 --> 22:22.167
Well, and Fisk sunk that ship.
Not Daredevil.

22:27.250 --> 22:28.333
Where's Matt?

22:28.875 --> 22:29.875
Karen?

22:33.042 --> 22:35.833
[sighs] Can't answer that...

22:36.792 --> 22:37.833
but he's safe.

22:40.583 --> 22:41.625
Okay.

22:43.708 --> 22:45.292
You think you know people...

22:55.208 --> 22:56.208
Here.

22:58.375 --> 22:59.417
Thanks.

23:03.875 --> 23:05.125
You do, you know.

23:13.125 --> 23:14.583
All right. [sighs]

23:17.500 --> 23:20.708
What do you need? And how much
is it gonna screw with my life?

23:22.500 --> 23:23.667
[chuckles softly]

23:25.292 --> 23:27.708
[Governor] To be honest,
I was expecting the call.

23:27.792 --> 23:29.833
I just wasn't expecting it from you.

23:30.667 --> 23:33.458
It's not often I'm surprised. [sighs]

23:34.542 --> 23:37.583
[Vanessa] You and I speak
a more similar language than my husband.

23:37.667 --> 23:39.375
[Governor] The Mayor, I understand.

23:40.167 --> 23:42.500
It's you, that's the mystery to me.

23:43.167 --> 23:46.417
Now, he... he's like the White Bull,
crashing through everything.

23:47.083 --> 23:48.458
Does that make you Europa?

23:48.542 --> 23:51.375
Oh. I'm no victim.

23:51.458 --> 23:53.042
I'm not entirely sure she was either.

23:54.125 --> 23:58.125
[breathes deeply] We can be candid
with each other, right?

23:58.208 --> 23:59.792
Of course, that's why I'm here.

24:01.417 --> 24:03.708
I don't like the way your husband
wields his power.

24:04.458 --> 24:05.792
I don't trust it,

24:05.875 --> 24:07.417
and it makes me nervous.

24:08.208 --> 24:09.958
I don't see Safer Streets,

24:10.500 --> 24:12.417
a thriving economy, and...

24:12.500 --> 24:14.792
neighborhood revitalization as problems.

24:15.417 --> 24:16.750
"New York Born Again."

24:17.500 --> 24:20.042
-A bit grandiose, don't you think?
-[both chuckle]

24:20.125 --> 24:23.417
My husband has big plans
for the city he loves.

24:25.583 --> 24:27.917
It'd be a shame if New York's progress

24:28.750 --> 24:32.333
was halted because of
unfortunate decisions.

24:33.333 --> 24:35.250
I said the Mayor gives me pause.

24:35.333 --> 24:36.500
You don't.

24:36.583 --> 24:40.167
The city shuts down businesses,
you unload them to Cooper and others,

24:40.250 --> 24:42.917
laying down the infrastructure
for long-term growth.

24:43.000 --> 24:44.292
It's shrewd...

24:45.417 --> 24:46.792
and ruthless.

24:46.875 --> 24:48.542
And I mean that as a compliment.

24:49.125 --> 24:50.542
I take it as one.

24:51.458 --> 24:52.542
Thank you.

24:53.167 --> 24:56.583
You could have done all of this
on your own.

24:57.417 --> 25:01.000
And yet, you chose to do it with Wilson.

25:02.125 --> 25:03.125
Why?

25:08.333 --> 25:09.750
I never thought it'd be him.

25:09.833 --> 25:11.458
[♪ eerie music playing]

25:12.750 --> 25:13.750
And then it was.

25:15.875 --> 25:18.083
And now I can't imagine it...

25:20.833 --> 25:22.083
being any other way.

25:24.958 --> 25:27.750
Can you temper his darker impulses?

25:29.958 --> 25:32.917
You want guarantees that I can't give you,

25:33.000 --> 25:34.667
but I can give you this...

25:35.417 --> 25:38.250
my husband loves New York,
and I love my husband.

25:39.833 --> 25:42.458
And I know how to bring out
the very best in him.

25:45.083 --> 25:47.125
Honestly, I... I couldn't sleep at night

25:47.208 --> 25:48.625
backing Mayor Fisk.

25:53.208 --> 25:56.417
But I can back Mayor and Mrs. Fisk.

25:59.125 --> 26:00.250
Thank you.

26:04.417 --> 26:05.792
-Thank you.
-Okay.

26:06.375 --> 26:09.000
Uh, we ran out of guac, bro,
but shit's still gonna be bussin'.

26:09.083 --> 26:11.333
[♪ hip-hop song playing
over speaker]

26:11.417 --> 26:14.292
Uh, welcome to Arriba Arepas.

26:14.375 --> 26:15.417
What do you want?

26:15.500 --> 26:17.333
Una arepa paisa, por favor.

26:19.167 --> 26:20.958
Oh, my gosh. A leprechaun.

26:21.042 --> 26:23.417
-Did you lose your pot of gold?
-Just shut the fuck up, Javi.

26:25.458 --> 26:27.208
I need you to do something for me.

26:28.208 --> 26:29.292
Fuck is this?

26:30.917 --> 26:32.875
I need you not to screw it up.

26:33.417 --> 26:35.167
Chill, I got you.

26:35.833 --> 26:37.625
I will seriously beat your ass.

26:37.708 --> 26:39.375
Ay, ay!

26:39.458 --> 26:40.625
You don't want that arepa?

26:41.417 --> 26:42.458
I... I guess not.

26:44.208 --> 26:46.375
Yeah, I'm not taking customers right now.
Give me one second.

26:47.542 --> 26:48.667
[doorbell dinging]

26:58.292 --> 26:59.458
[squeaks]

27:01.417 --> 27:02.875
All right, wrap it up! Let's go.

27:02.958 --> 27:03.958
Get lost!

27:05.125 --> 27:06.417
[officer] CSI's not done.

27:06.500 --> 27:09.125
Vigilante crimes. Task Force jurisdiction.

27:09.208 --> 27:10.208
What, are you pulling rank?

27:10.292 --> 27:11.292
[Matt] Let's go!

27:11.875 --> 27:13.333
Want me to call my friends?

27:15.667 --> 27:17.708
[officer] Hate these Task Force pricks.

27:17.792 --> 27:19.208
-[door opens]
-[doorbell dinging]

27:22.208 --> 27:23.458
-[door closes]
-[doorbell dinging]

27:27.250 --> 27:29.417
[♪ eerie music playing]

27:30.500 --> 27:31.667
[Matt] Jesus Christ.

27:38.667 --> 27:39.708
[sniffs]

27:46.333 --> 27:48.000
[squeaks]

27:48.750 --> 27:49.750
[sniffs]

27:50.583 --> 27:51.875
[grunts softly]

28:08.250 --> 28:09.458
[chuckles]

28:09.542 --> 28:10.750
[bell tolling]

28:16.542 --> 28:18.375
[♪ somber choir music playing]

28:23.458 --> 28:24.958
[bell tolling]

28:26.167 --> 28:27.167
[sighs softly]

28:49.125 --> 28:50.417
[shuddering breaths]

28:56.875 --> 28:57.958
[grunts softly]

29:07.625 --> 29:08.750
"Saint Lucia,

29:08.833 --> 29:10.750
"your beautiful name signifies light.

29:11.500 --> 29:14.250
"By the light of the faith
that God bestowed upon you...

29:14.833 --> 29:19.417
"increase and preserve this light
in my soul so that I may avoid evil,

29:19.500 --> 29:21.917
"be zealous in the performance
of good works...

29:22.875 --> 29:26.292
"And abhor nothing so much
as the darkness of evil and sin.

29:27.625 --> 29:28.625
"Amen."

29:29.750 --> 29:31.167
[seminarian] Haven't heard
that one in a long time.

29:34.458 --> 29:35.458
I, uh...

29:36.042 --> 29:37.375
I knew a boy.

29:37.458 --> 29:39.417
Uh, he was blind.

29:40.083 --> 29:42.583
Saint Lucia got him through
some tough times.

29:44.625 --> 29:46.000
You seem troubled, officer.

29:48.542 --> 29:50.542
Actually, I... I, uh,
grew up in this church.

29:52.250 --> 29:53.333
Haven't been back in a minute.

29:54.167 --> 29:55.667
[seminarian] Tell me, what--
What brings you back?

30:02.875 --> 30:05.125
I found that at a murder scene today.

30:07.333 --> 30:09.292
These tokens are available
to all our parishioners.

30:09.375 --> 30:10.875
So I couldn't possibly know who left this.

30:13.625 --> 30:15.292
[heart thumping]

30:17.000 --> 30:18.458
Tell me who you think...

30:19.292 --> 30:20.292
left it.

30:22.542 --> 30:24.833
[breathes deeply]

30:26.167 --> 30:27.208
There was a man.

30:28.208 --> 30:30.083
He came looking for a nun
who used to be assigned here.

30:30.917 --> 30:31.917
This man...

30:32.583 --> 30:34.125
uh, what did he want?

30:34.833 --> 30:36.333
He came looking for, um...

30:37.292 --> 30:38.792
I-- I don't know.

30:39.542 --> 30:41.375
Counsel. Penance.

30:41.458 --> 30:42.458
I told him

30:42.542 --> 30:45.125
I wasn't a priest yet--
He held a knife on me.

30:45.708 --> 30:46.708
And what did he say?

30:49.333 --> 30:50.625
Listen to me...

30:51.750 --> 30:52.750
This man...

30:54.208 --> 30:55.583
is a killer.

30:55.667 --> 30:58.458
Even so, I can't turn someone over
to the police.

30:59.333 --> 31:00.917
His judgment is not for us to say.

31:01.000 --> 31:03.583
Yeah, I'm not gonna debate with you
whether or not he deserves grace...

31:04.583 --> 31:06.000
but I do need to find him,

31:06.083 --> 31:07.625
or others will die.

31:10.583 --> 31:11.833
What will you do...

31:13.000 --> 31:14.125
when you find him?

31:17.000 --> 31:18.000
I won't kill him.

31:23.417 --> 31:26.000
He told me he wakes every morning
to the sound of the church bells.

31:26.625 --> 31:28.875
And he watches me open the doors
for morning mass.

31:29.917 --> 31:31.208
Watches from where?

31:32.000 --> 31:33.375
His window.

31:33.458 --> 31:35.792
-[bell tolling]
-[indistinct chatter]

31:38.458 --> 31:40.000
[horn honking]

31:43.292 --> 31:44.333
[Dex] Let me help you with that.

31:47.625 --> 31:48.708
See you tomorrow.

31:49.292 --> 31:51.083
Such a nice boy.

31:52.958 --> 31:54.000
[coin clinks]

31:55.125 --> 31:56.458
[coins jingling]

31:56.542 --> 31:58.750
[truck beeping]

32:01.292 --> 32:02.292
[switch clicks]

32:10.208 --> 32:12.083
[♪ soft music playing over CD player]

32:15.042 --> 32:16.167
[♪ music stops]

32:17.000 --> 32:18.500
-[Dex grunts]
-[CD whooshing]

32:19.417 --> 32:20.417
[Daredevil yells]

32:21.583 --> 32:23.833
[both grunting]

32:25.583 --> 32:26.917
[both grunting]

32:34.417 --> 32:35.667
[both yell]

32:36.500 --> 32:39.125
-[grunts]
-[groans, breathes heavily]

32:42.667 --> 32:43.917
[Dex grunts]

32:47.000 --> 32:49.458
-[Daredevil yells]
-[Dex grunts]

32:49.542 --> 32:51.000
I'm on your side.

32:51.083 --> 32:52.583
[both grunting]

32:56.500 --> 32:58.792
[screams] What are you doing to my Tony?

33:00.375 --> 33:01.625
[breathing heavily]

33:04.292 --> 33:05.958
-[Mrs. Smithers screams]
-[Daredevil groans]

33:06.042 --> 33:07.333
[Dex grunts]

33:07.417 --> 33:08.417
Stop!

33:08.500 --> 33:09.625
-One good deed!
-[grunts]

33:09.708 --> 33:11.875
One good deed!

33:11.958 --> 33:13.208
Put the gun down!

33:13.292 --> 33:14.708
What I did--

33:14.792 --> 33:17.833
-What that woman had me do...
-[Daredevil] No, no, no, no, no.

33:17.917 --> 33:19.333
-...to your friend...
-Don't you bring him up!

33:19.917 --> 33:21.583
Don't you dare bring him up!
Not like this!

33:21.667 --> 33:23.000
But I had to get out.

33:23.500 --> 33:25.042
I had to get my mind back.

33:26.042 --> 33:27.125
And one good deed,

33:28.375 --> 33:29.667
it levels the scales again.

33:29.750 --> 33:32.750
Oh! Uh... [chuckling]

33:32.833 --> 33:34.708
-All right. Okay.
-[Mrs. Smithers] No!

33:34.792 --> 33:35.833
What is the, uh--

33:35.917 --> 33:37.917
What is this, uh, one good deed?

33:38.000 --> 33:39.375
What is it you wanna do?

33:39.458 --> 33:41.250
[panting] What you wouldn't do.

33:42.500 --> 33:43.750
What you won't do.

33:44.458 --> 33:47.167
[sighs] Fisk. [exhales]

33:47.250 --> 33:48.292
I can't...

33:48.375 --> 33:50.500
I can't let you make a martyr out of him.

33:51.625 --> 33:53.083
I'm gonna make things right.

33:54.542 --> 33:55.542
I'm gonna help you.

33:55.625 --> 33:57.750
Please. Look, just calm down.

33:59.458 --> 34:00.583
I am calm.

34:00.667 --> 34:01.875
-[Daredevil grunts]
-[Dex grunts]

34:04.625 --> 34:06.000
[meows]

34:07.000 --> 34:09.083
-[Mrs. Smithers speaking Polish]
-[grunting]

34:11.875 --> 34:13.417
[scooter engine revving]

34:13.500 --> 34:15.000
[Daredevil grunting]

34:17.667 --> 34:18.958
-[Dex grunts]
-[man grunting]

34:19.042 --> 34:20.208
[tires screech]

34:21.542 --> 34:22.833
[grunts]

34:22.917 --> 34:24.167
[engine accelerating]

34:24.958 --> 34:26.292
[panting]

34:28.833 --> 34:31.167
[Christofi in English] My name
is Christofi Savva.

34:31.750 --> 34:34.417
I was the First Mate on the Northern Star.

34:35.042 --> 34:38.125
My Captain, Achilleo Kyriacou,

34:38.208 --> 34:39.625
scuttled the ship.

34:39.708 --> 34:42.958
We were under orders to sink the ship

34:43.042 --> 34:44.458
if it was ever boarded.

34:45.583 --> 34:47.000
Why was that?

34:48.417 --> 34:51.375
Because the Northern Star
was carrying weapons,

34:51.458 --> 34:53.250
military grade, very illegal.

34:54.375 --> 34:58.833
And who was the one
who ordered you to scuttle the ship?

34:59.417 --> 35:00.958
Achilleo called him...

35:01.042 --> 35:03.000
Vasillias tou Enklimatos,

35:03.083 --> 35:04.292
the Kingpin...

35:05.042 --> 35:07.125
but we knew it was the Mayor.

35:08.333 --> 35:09.833
There was no customs check.

35:10.542 --> 35:14.125
We did not have to present
a bill of lading or manifest.

35:14.750 --> 35:17.375
We were never registered with Coast Guard,

35:17.458 --> 35:18.958
Homeland Security, none of it.

35:19.042 --> 35:21.333
I've been to many ports
all over this world.

35:22.333 --> 35:24.375
In order to make that happen...

35:25.500 --> 35:26.833
you have to own the city.

35:27.708 --> 35:29.458
Uh, "own the city" is correct?

35:30.375 --> 35:32.375
Yeah, in this case, it just might be.

35:34.167 --> 35:37.833
You said you were under orders
to scuttle the Northern Star

35:37.917 --> 35:39.250
if it was boarded.

35:40.875 --> 35:42.000
Who boarded the vessel?

35:42.833 --> 35:43.917
Coast Guard?

35:44.708 --> 35:46.542
Uh, no.

35:46.625 --> 35:47.625
One man.

35:49.500 --> 35:50.667
Daredevil.

35:55.083 --> 35:56.708
[Kirsten] The marshals are on their way.

35:56.792 --> 35:58.083
They'll keep you safe.

36:03.458 --> 36:05.875
[indistinct chatter]

36:05.958 --> 36:06.958
[Daniel] Hello.

36:07.458 --> 36:08.875
-[BB chuckles]
-Look at that.

36:08.958 --> 36:10.167
Ringside, baby.

36:10.708 --> 36:12.125
We're gonna be so close, you and me,

36:12.208 --> 36:13.708
that we're gonna be
covered in sweat tonight.

36:14.833 --> 36:17.333
That didn't come out
how it sounded in your head.

36:17.417 --> 36:20.500
Did not. You know what? I was saying it,
and I sort of realized

36:20.583 --> 36:23.167
as it was coming out that
it wasn't really what I meant.

36:23.250 --> 36:24.875
-So, uh...
-Mm.

36:24.958 --> 36:26.333
Anyways, um...

36:26.833 --> 36:28.500
thank you for inviting me.

36:29.500 --> 36:30.500
Of course.

36:30.583 --> 36:32.458
Yo! You're BB.

36:33.042 --> 36:34.375
Like The BB Report.

36:34.917 --> 36:36.458
Yeah, that... that's me. You watch that?

36:36.542 --> 36:37.750
Everybody watches it.

36:37.833 --> 36:39.375
My brother, my cousin, my tía.

36:39.458 --> 36:40.458
Yo, they're obsessed.

36:40.542 --> 36:41.875
[chuckles]

36:41.958 --> 36:44.000
Oh, can I get a pic?
It's gonna blow their mind.

36:44.083 --> 36:45.250
Yeah, for sure. Come on.

36:46.958 --> 36:48.125
[camera shutter clicks]

36:55.333 --> 36:56.708
Yo, appreciate you.

36:57.250 --> 36:58.500
My bad.

37:00.792 --> 37:02.333
[♪ tense music playing]

37:07.875 --> 37:10.125
Didn't realize
I was on a date with a celebrity.

37:10.792 --> 37:11.792
Come on.

37:13.000 --> 37:15.792
I'm not a celebrity and not a date.

37:17.042 --> 37:18.042
Yeah, not yet.

37:19.667 --> 37:21.333
[♪ "At A Disadvantage"
by Slick Naim playing]

37:24.292 --> 37:25.500
[siren blaring]

37:28.750 --> 37:29.750
[trainer] Make a fist.

37:30.625 --> 37:31.792
-Feel good?
-[Fisk] Yeah.

37:33.458 --> 37:34.708
Uh, that's not necessary.

37:34.792 --> 37:36.208
He'll never lay a glove on me.

37:36.292 --> 37:38.875
[trainer chuckles] I like
your style, Mayor.

37:41.708 --> 37:43.000
Anything?

37:43.083 --> 37:46.125
No. We have men on rooftops, subways,

37:46.208 --> 37:47.625
every entrance, and exit.

37:47.708 --> 37:50.500
Inside's covered, too.
We have Task Force in plainclothes

37:50.583 --> 37:52.583
and uniforms lugging serious firepower,

37:52.667 --> 37:53.833
so nothing's getting in.

37:54.542 --> 37:56.125
We'll need an entrance cleared.

37:58.333 --> 38:00.042
Preferably, the front doors.

38:02.375 --> 38:04.083
Sir, uh, I don't think tying yourself

38:04.167 --> 38:05.875
-to the stake is a very...
-[phone vibrating]

38:07.792 --> 38:09.000
...good idea.

38:10.417 --> 38:12.250
[Fisk] Looks like
you have somewhere to be.

38:16.667 --> 38:17.958
I'm not going anywhere...

38:18.458 --> 38:20.875
especially if you wanna
dangle yourself out as bait.

38:21.458 --> 38:22.833
Buck...

38:22.917 --> 38:23.917
go.

38:25.458 --> 38:27.292
We can't have any loose ends.

38:29.042 --> 38:30.250
[Buck sighs]

38:34.458 --> 38:35.500
[Fisk sighs]

38:35.583 --> 38:37.000
Don't worry, sir. Me and North got it.

38:37.958 --> 38:40.167
[rapper] ♪ I was working,
I couldn't understand it ♪

38:40.833 --> 38:43.208
♪ I was hurting, I was in a panic ♪

38:43.292 --> 38:45.667
♪ See, I felt like
I ain't meet the standards ♪

38:46.375 --> 38:48.125
♪ But yet, I made it at a disadvantage ♪

38:48.208 --> 38:49.208
[all cheering]

38:49.292 --> 38:51.208
♪ Yes, I made it at a disadvantage ♪

38:51.292 --> 38:54.417
♪ Yes, I made it at a disadvantage ♪

38:54.500 --> 38:56.292
♪ Yes, I made it at a disadvantage ♪

38:56.375 --> 38:58.625
-[Daniel] All right. I got prezzies.
-[BB] Ooh.

38:58.708 --> 39:00.750
I thought you're a foam finger kinda lady.

39:00.833 --> 39:01.958
[scoffs] I'm not.

39:02.042 --> 39:03.792
[Daniel] And there you go.

39:03.875 --> 39:05.167
Oh. Thank you.

39:05.250 --> 39:06.417
[Daniel] Look at this.

39:06.500 --> 39:07.833
Bobblehead Fisk, uh?

39:08.833 --> 39:10.542
-Very realistic.
-[Sheila chuckles]

39:10.625 --> 39:11.750
Look at that.

39:11.833 --> 39:13.417
Pure class.

39:14.083 --> 39:15.375
I hope you got the discount.

39:17.042 --> 39:18.333
There's a discount?

39:19.333 --> 39:20.333
Shit.

39:25.208 --> 39:27.375
Ladies and gentlemen,

39:27.458 --> 39:29.042
proud New Yorkers,

39:29.125 --> 39:32.000
welcome to Scrappin' In The Kitchen,

39:32.083 --> 39:37.583
benefiting the New York Born Again
revitalization project.

39:37.667 --> 39:40.833
The main event
will consist of three rounds.

39:40.917 --> 39:43.375
Winner determined by knockout,

39:43.458 --> 39:46.083
TKO, or points.

39:46.167 --> 39:48.583
Now, get out of your seats,

39:48.667 --> 39:52.167
clap your hands, and welcome--

39:52.250 --> 39:53.750
In purple trunks,

39:53.833 --> 39:56.625
weighing in at 235 pounds

39:56.708 --> 39:59.875
with a professional record
of thirty-two and two,

39:59.958 --> 40:03.667
-Mike "The Matterhorn" Melendez!
-[booing]

40:03.750 --> 40:07.292
And in the white corner,

40:07.375 --> 40:10.333
our hometown hero of Hell's Kitchen,

40:10.417 --> 40:12.042
wearing white trunks,

40:12.125 --> 40:15.167
weighing in at 325 pounds,

40:15.250 --> 40:18.125
with no professional boxing record,

40:18.208 --> 40:23.083
Mayor Wilson "Wildcard" Fisk!

40:23.167 --> 40:25.250
[all cheering]

40:25.333 --> 40:27.375
[♪ dramatic music playing]

40:27.833 --> 40:29.708
-[man 1] Yeah!
-[man 2] Boo!

40:29.792 --> 40:30.833
[all applauding]

40:51.875 --> 40:54.542
-[man 3] Boo!
-Yeah! [chanting] Fisk! Fisk! Fisk!

40:54.625 --> 40:56.708
Fisk! Fisk! Fisk! Fisk!

40:56.792 --> 40:58.125
Fisk!

41:11.375 --> 41:12.792
[referee] I want a clean fight.

41:12.875 --> 41:14.292
Nothing below the belt.

41:14.375 --> 41:16.667
Obey my commands.
Defend yourselves at all times.

41:16.750 --> 41:17.917
Touch gloves.

41:19.917 --> 41:21.292
[thuds]

41:25.458 --> 41:26.458
[all cheering]

41:27.667 --> 41:29.000
[man 4] Yeah!

41:31.458 --> 41:33.250
[♪ dramatic music continues]

41:51.000 --> 41:52.250
[bell dings]

41:52.333 --> 41:53.583
[Fisk breathing raggedly]

41:56.042 --> 41:57.792
-[Fisk grunts]
-[groans]

42:00.875 --> 42:04.000
[grunts, groans]

42:06.042 --> 42:07.500
Yeah! Yes!

42:07.583 --> 42:08.667
Let's go!

42:08.750 --> 42:10.875
That what you want? Fine!

42:10.958 --> 42:12.125
[Fisk yells]

42:19.000 --> 42:20.583
[tires screech]

42:25.792 --> 42:27.208
-[gunshots]
-[officers grunt]

42:27.917 --> 42:30.625
[both grunting]

42:35.708 --> 42:36.792
Hello, Mr. Savva.

42:40.500 --> 42:41.875
-[both grunting]
-[all cheering]

42:42.875 --> 42:44.042
[heavy breathing]

42:46.292 --> 42:47.958
[Fisk grunting]

42:49.042 --> 42:51.000
-[Mike groans]
-[bell dinging]

42:51.083 --> 42:53.458
[Fisk yelling]

42:53.542 --> 42:55.792
-Yeah! Yes! Yes!
-Oh, my God.

42:57.417 --> 42:59.083
[all cheering]

43:01.042 --> 43:03.083
[camera shutter clicking]

43:04.167 --> 43:06.250
[grunts, breathes heavily]

43:11.875 --> 43:13.792
Christofi's been taken care of.

43:14.750 --> 43:15.750
All right.

43:22.083 --> 43:24.667
-[breathes deeply]
-[bell dinging]

43:27.375 --> 43:29.208
[all cheering]

43:31.250 --> 43:33.292
[both grunting]

43:36.333 --> 43:37.792
[woman] Yeah!

43:37.875 --> 43:38.875
Yeah!

43:38.958 --> 43:41.167
[all cheering]

43:42.000 --> 43:43.625
[both grunting]

43:48.833 --> 43:51.042
[Fisk breathing heavily]

43:53.792 --> 43:55.500
[grunts softly]

43:55.583 --> 43:57.000
[straining]

44:00.458 --> 44:01.500
[Fisk breathing heavily]

44:02.000 --> 44:03.750
[Fisk grunts]

44:06.375 --> 44:08.917
[grunts, yells]

44:11.625 --> 44:13.542
[thuds]

44:14.583 --> 44:15.958
-[yells]
-[groans]

44:16.708 --> 44:18.375
[blood splattering]

44:24.500 --> 44:26.125
[woman screams] Oh!

44:26.208 --> 44:27.583
[people murmuring softly]

44:38.625 --> 44:40.167
[bell dinging]

44:46.792 --> 44:48.792
[all applauding, cheering]

45:00.625 --> 45:02.083
[bell dinging]

45:03.125 --> 45:04.583
[all cheering]

45:10.083 --> 45:11.083
Yeah!

45:11.167 --> 45:12.208
Oh, my God.

45:13.208 --> 45:16.250
-[camera shutter clicking]
-[cheering continues]

45:32.250 --> 45:33.625
You came.

45:34.417 --> 45:35.625
With a win.

45:36.500 --> 45:38.208
-I told you not to come.
-Kiss me.

45:38.292 --> 45:39.292
Listen to me.

45:39.375 --> 45:40.750
Kiss me.

45:44.083 --> 45:45.250
You need to go now.

45:45.333 --> 45:46.625
[officer grunts]

45:50.417 --> 45:52.208
[woman screaming]

45:55.083 --> 45:56.542
[both grunting]

45:56.625 --> 45:58.292
Get her out of here!

45:58.375 --> 45:59.625
[Vanessa gasps]

45:59.708 --> 46:01.750
[clamoring]

46:05.208 --> 46:07.583
-[Bullseye grunts]
-[grunts]

46:07.667 --> 46:09.125
[woman screaming]

46:09.208 --> 46:10.708
-[Bullseye grunts]
-[grunts]

46:10.792 --> 46:12.375
[officer] Get out of the way. Get down.

46:12.458 --> 46:15.292
-[Bullseye grunts]
-[grunts]

46:15.375 --> 46:16.375
[Fisk] Let me go!

46:18.250 --> 46:19.458
Get her out of here now!

46:21.250 --> 46:22.292
Shoot him down!

46:26.833 --> 46:27.917
Get her out of here!

46:29.667 --> 46:31.792
-[Vanessa grunts]
-[Fisk] Get her out!

46:35.500 --> 46:36.708
[Bullseye grunts]

46:50.042 --> 46:51.500
[Bullseye grunts]

46:55.250 --> 46:56.583
[grunts wearily]

46:58.625 --> 46:59.750
[Daredevil grunts]

47:01.208 --> 47:03.000
[Daredevil grunting]

47:03.083 --> 47:04.333
[Bullseye grunts]

47:04.417 --> 47:05.958
[Daredevil grunts]

47:06.542 --> 47:07.583
[both grunting]

47:07.667 --> 47:08.917
[gunshots]

47:11.958 --> 47:13.833
[both grunting]

47:19.750 --> 47:20.750
[Bullseye groans]

47:22.458 --> 47:23.458
[Fisk] Go get them!

47:23.917 --> 47:24.917
Now!

47:27.708 --> 47:29.625
[officer] Fifteen. Let's go! Let's go!

47:29.708 --> 47:32.292
[officers shouting indistinctly]

47:33.375 --> 47:35.750
-[Vanessa] Wilson...
-[pants]

47:40.792 --> 47:43.000
[♪ melancholy music playing]

47:44.125 --> 47:45.125
[Vanessa gasps]

47:46.917 --> 47:48.417
[breathing heavily]

47:56.958 --> 47:59.000
[Vanessa gasps]

48:04.125 --> 48:06.167
[sniffles] Get an ambulance!

48:07.125 --> 48:08.458
Somebody, please!

48:10.500 --> 48:12.125
[shuddering]

48:16.292 --> 48:17.667
[muffled yelling]

48:28.542 --> 48:30.417
[♪ eerie music playing]
